# Zeek Logs to SQLite - Cron Schedule
# 
# This crontab entry runs the zeek-to-sqlite script every 6 hours
# Adjust the schedule as needed using standard cron syntax:
#   minute hour day month weekday
#
# Examples:
#   Every 6 hours: 0 */6 * * *
#   Every 4 hours: 0 */4 * * *
#   Every hour: 0 * * * *
#   Daily at 2 AM: 0 2 * * *
#
# To install:
#   1. Edit this file with your desired schedule
#   2. Run: crontab -e
#   3. Add the line below (adjust path as needed)
#   4. Save and exit
#
# Make sure the script is executable:
#   chmod +x /path/to/zeek-home-network/zeek-to-sqlite-cron.sh

# Run every 6 hours at the top of the hour (00:00, 06:00, 12:00, 18:00)
# IMPORTANT: Replace /path/to/zeek-home-network with the actual path where you cloned the repo
0 */6 * * * /home/pi/zeek-home-network/zeek-to-sqlite-cron.sh

# Alternative: Run every 6 hours at specific times (02:00, 08:00, 14:00, 20:00)
# 0 2,8,14,20 * * * /path/to/zeek-home-network/zeek-to-sqlite-cron.sh

